subject: ethernet: Change the behavior of setting VLANEnable
commitMessage:
ethernet: Change the behavior of setting VLANEnable

In current implementation, setting VLANEnable to true does nothing
while setting to false will essentially delete the VLAN from system,
which is not a reasonable behavior for Redfish. PATCH requests should
never delete a resource. This patch changes the behavior to changing
the NICEnabled property of VLAN interface, which essentially enables/
disables the VLAN interface.

Tested:
Verified PATCH {"VLANEnable": false} no longer deletes the interface
and the NICEnabled property on DBus is successfully changed.

Change-Id: I8c47f6f2987fed576ba36c215f29bc03c6e9182b
Signed-off-by: Jiaqing Zhao <jiaqing.zhao@intel.com>

nit: why does the indent change here?
Clang-format auto formatted like this

I may not be understanding all of the changes being made, and how they interlock. Here are some observations with regard to the changes.

BTW, have you run the Redfish Service Validator across this? If I'm correct about the VLANs -> VLAN change the validator might have found that for you.
Shouldn't "/VLANs/" be "/VLAN/"? Pretty much globally in this schema?

It's VLANs here, bmcweb is still implementing the deprecated VLanNetworkInterface schema, the VLANs is a link to VLanNetworkInterface collection.

https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/52951
Some background disscussion is here.

> A limitation is that latest schema does not provide a proper way to create VLANs. I had a discussion in redfish from at https://redfishforum.com/thread/619/proper-create-using-ethernetinterface-schema
> 
> My proposal is to keep using the deprecated VLanNetworkInterface for creating/deleting VLANs, while also exposes the VLAN interfaces under /​redfish/​v1/​Managers/​bmc/​EthernetInterfaces/​ for configuring them. This workaround will be here until redfish spec reached a solution, after that, remove the VLANs property. This patchset is the first stage of moving to the new way.
Ack

This doesn't make much sense to me. VLANEnable is a R/W element. It seems like the Redfish user will want to *write* this element with an true/false to enable/disable the VLAN independently of the NIC.

Does it make sense to make ethData contain a vlanSet containing an ID and Enable state for a list of VLANs?

I'm uncertain if you also qualify this with nicEnabled too. In some ways that seems superflous because the physical NIC being disabled will take this down too.

In phosphor-networkd, VLAN is a virtual interface that have it's own DBus properties, all interfaces are listed in a "plain" way like:
/xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth0
/xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth0_100
/xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth0_200
/xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth1

VLAN virtual interfaces has its own configuration that is somewhat indepenedent from the physical NIC, including the NICEnable property.

> Does it make sense to make ethData contain a vlanSet containing an ID and Enable state for a list of VLANs?

No, each interface can have at most one VLAN ID. The association is done by the interface names, like eth0_100, eth0_200 are associated to eth0 in the example above.

There is a detailed discussion in my previously merged https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/52951 about this concern.

> In some ways that seems superflous because the physical NIC being disabled will take this down too.

Yeah disabling the physical interface will disable the related VLAN interfaces. But users may only want to disable only eth_100 but keep eth0_200 and the physical eth0 enabled.
Ack

Is this 'if' clause necessary? The caller has already confirmed ethData.vlanId is non-null.
In addition, isn't vlanId the same as ifaceId in this instance?
The two terms appear to be synonymous to me.
I think this function is unnecessary as it only fills some json property, I will make another patch to remove it.
Ack
The NIC may have more than one VLAN. There needs to be a mechanism for iterating over all of the VLANs in the collection.

This implements the Redfish VLanNetworkInterface schema, each resourece only have 1 VLAN ID. For multiple VLAN ID, the iteration is done when getting the collection at /​redfish/​v1/​Managers/​{ManagerId}/​EthernetInterfaces/​{EthernetInterfaceId}/​VLANs/.
Ack

Shouldn't this be "/VLAN/"?
EthernetInterfaces/eth0/VLAN/17   For example?

VLANs is the collection
VLAN is the element
Schema is /​redfish/​v1/​Managers/​{ManagerId}/​EthernetInterfaces/​{EthernetInterfaceId}/​VLANs/​{VLanNetworkInterfaceId}. If VLAN, that just a property, no more url handlers.
Ack
IMO *vlanEnable is the value to be returned for the ethx/VLAN/vlanId GET action.
The get handler is also changed.
It's from readJsonPatch() above.
Ack
